><A HREF="gc.htm"> Of God and His Creatures</a><hr><p>
As is the ease with those whose god is their belly
(Phil. iii, 19): i.e., who live for drink, and will do
anything to get it, and for the lusts of the lower belly:
that is their 'religion,' an insult to the living God.

